<item>
            <title>[LU-11653] hsm: copytool registration should trigger request dispatching from the coordinator</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11653</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the coordinator wakes up, it checks that something worth its attention has happened, otherwise it simply goes back to sleep.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is possible for the coordinator to have several waiting requests in its llog but no copytool to process them. In this situation, when a copytool registers to the coordinator, the coordinator should wake up and try to schedule requests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The fix is pretty simple, we should call &lt;tt&gt;mdt_hsm_cdt_event()&lt;/tt&gt; from &lt;tt&gt;mdt_hsm_agent_register()&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
